wi_steps.step_desc:
Prepare the components listed:
- 1) Body stand rear x2
- 2) Body stand front x2
- 3) Absorber bracket x2
- 4) Piston Housing x4
- 5) Car tail x1
- 6) Car casing x1
- S1) Screw (d) 3mm (l) 11mm x4
- S2) Screw (d) 3mm (l) 13.5mm x4
- S3) Washer screw (od) 8mm (id) 2.5mm (l) 8.8mm x2

1) Locate these two square holes in part No. 3.
2) Locate this square joint in part No. 1 and part No. 2.

3) Connect them and make sure that it is pointing upwards.
4) It should look like these, part No. 1 in one pair and part No. 2 in one pair.

PLEASE IGNORE THE RED COLOUR ON THE PARTS IT IS DUE TO THE LIGHTING.
5) S1 is slightly shorter than S2.

6) Hold down part No. 1 or part No. 2 firmly and screw it with S1. Make sure to push down the screwdriver when you screw it.
7) It should look like this.

PLEASE IGNORE THE RED COLOUR ON PARTS IT IS DUE TO LIGHTING.

9) Place the screw (S2) on part No. 4. 
10) Screw it on the holes shown just now. Do it for all 4 holes. PLEASE DO NOT OVER TIGHTEN IT, BUT NOT LOOSE.
11) Make sure that it can be moved a bit.

14) Flip over the car
15) Locate the 2 holes at the rear side of the car.

16) Place the car tail as shown.
17) Screw it with S3.
